        "body": "**Removed explicit timeout parameter makes inline task timeout behavior implicit and hard to audit**\n\nThe commit removed `session_timeout=600` from _build_inline_task(), replacing it with reliance on the model's default (now 3600s). While this reduces duplication, it makes the timeout value implicit in the code. Code reviewers and maintainers must now consult factory/models.py to understand what timeout an inline task gets. The old explicit value was more discoverable during code review. Additionally, there is no CLI flag (e.g., `--session-timeout`) to override the timeout for individual inline tasks.\n\nRaised by: claude-code\n\nSuggested fix: Add optional `session_timeout: Optional[int] = None` parameter to _build_inline_task(). If provided, pass it to CoderConfig(); if None, use the model default. Expose via CLI with `typer.Option(None, '--session-timeout', help=...)`. Add docstring: 'session_timeout: Max seconds per coder iteration (default: 3600 from CoderConfig)'",
