- [Warning] factory/runner.py:210-212 Add documentation explaining compound timeout effects: per-iteration max runtime with all phases enabled, total maximum runtime for max_iterations cycles, and validation that actual workloads fit comfortably within these limits.
  description: Each coder iteration gets the full `session_timeout` of 3600s. With `max_iterations=3` (default), the coder phase alone can consume 3×3600s = 10,800s (3 hours). Additionally, each iteration can trigger eval (300s), crucible (600s), and evaluator (120s) phases if enabled. Total per-iteration: 3600 + 300 + 600 + 120 = 4620s (77 minutes). Total for 3 iterations: ~13,800s (3.8 hours). The commit and code comments do NOT document these compounding effects, validate that workloads fit within these boundaries, or provide baseline metrics. This creates uncertainty about whether 3600s is appropriate or excessive, and masks the actual maximum runtime from task designers.
