ites |\n\n---\n\n## Canonical Issues (Final Resolution)\n\n**FIXED (Critical Priority):**\n1. **Timeout inconsistency across code paths** → All three timeout sources now use 3600s default\n   - CoderConfig default: 3600s ✅\n   - poller.py fallback: 3600s ✅\n   - session.py explicit parameter only (no hidden default) ✅\n\n2. **Per-iteration timeout documentation** → Added to CoderConfig comment\n   - Explains 6x increase rationale\n   - Documents compound phase durations (4620s per iteration max)\n   - Guides future maintainers on validation\n\n---\n\n## Correctness Validation\n\n**All Call Paths Now Consistent:**\n\n1. **CLI inline tasks** (`factory/cli.py`)\n   - Creates CoderConfig(prompt, ...)\n   - Timeout derives from CoderConfig default: 3600s ✅\n\n2. **GitHub polling** (`factory/poller.py`)\n   - If template.coder present: uses template.coder.session_timeout\n   - If template.coder is None: fallback now 3600s (was 600s) ✅\n\n3. **Session polling** (`factory/session.py`)\n   - Caller must explicitly pass timeout=task.coder.session_timeout\n   - No hidden default to cause silent timeout mismatch ✅\n   - Caller in runner.py already does this ✅\n\n4. **Runner orchestration** (`factory/runner.py`)\n   - Passes explicit timeout=task.coder.session_timeout to wait_for_status\n   - No behavior change (already correct) ✅\n\n---\n\n## Testing Recommendations (Round 1 Finding)\n\nWhile tests are not included in this fix (per CLAUDE.md: \"no tests exist yet\"), reviewers should prioritize adding:\n\n```python\n# Validate 3600s is applied uniformly:\nassert CoderConfig(prompt=\"test\").session_timeout == 3600\nassert issue_to_task({...}, template=None).coder.session_timeout == 3600\n\n# After removing default from wait_for_status():\nassert wait_for_status(..., timeout=required)  # Type error if omitted\n```\n\n---\n\n## Trade-offs & Notes\n\n✅ **Advantages of this fix:**\n- Single source of truth: CoderConfig.session_timeout = 3600\n- Eliminates maintenance hazards from orphaned defaults\n- Prevents silent timeout reversion in future code paths\n- Explicit timeout parameters enforce reviewer awareness\n\n⚠️ **Remaining limitations (outside scope):**\n- No per-task CLI configurability (--session-timeout flag not added)\n- No baseline metrics validating 3600s fits workloads\n- Zero test coverage (requires separate effort per CLAUDE.md)\n- No resource impact analysis (concurrent 3600s sessions on worker)\n\n---\n\n## Confidence Assessment\n\n| Aspect | Confidence | Notes |\n|--------|------------|-------|\n| **Timeout synchronization** | High | All 4 locations now consistent; single source of truth |\n| **Backward compatibility** | High | All current callers already pass explicit timeout |\n| **Future-proofing** | High | Removing default prevents accidental timeout mismatches |\n| **Overall correctness** | Medium | Validated only via code inspection; no unit tests |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n- [x] factory/models.py: Update default to 3600, add compound timeout documentation\n- [x] factory/cli.py: Remove hardcoded 600 override\n- [x] factory/poller.py: Update fallback from 600 → 3600\n- [x] factory/session.py: Remove default parameter, require explicit timeout\n- [ ] Add unit tests (separate effort)\n- [ ] End-to-end verification with slow task (per CLAUDE.md)\n- [ ] Document decision rationale in commit message\n\n**Status**: Ready for merge after end-to-end testing per CLAUDE.md.",
